Sure! Below is a simple HTML file that implements a game where you click a blue button to earn points. The code includes embedded CSS for styling and JavaScript for functionality, all within a single code block.

```html
<!DOCTYPE html>
<html lang="en">
<head>
    <meta charset="UTF-8">
    <meta name="viewport" content="width=device-width, initial-scale=1.0">
    <title>Click the Blue Button Game</title>
    <style>
        body {
            display: flex;
            flex-direction: column;
            align-items: center;
            justify-content: center;
            height: 100vh;
            background-color: #f0f0f0;
            font-family: Arial, sans-serif;
        }
        h1 {
            color: #333;
        }
        #score {
            font-size: 24px;
            margin: 20px 0;
        }
        #clickButton {
            padding: 15px 30px;
            font-size: 20px;
            color: white;
            background-color: blue;
            border: none;
            border-radius: 5px;
            cursor: pointer;
            transition: background-color 0.3s;
        }
        #clickButton:hover {
            background-color: darkblue;
        }
    </style>
</head>
<body>

    <h1>Click the Blue Button Game</h1>
    <div id="score">Score: 0</div>
    <button id="clickButton">Click Me!</button>

    <script>
        let score = 0;

        const scoreDisplay = document.getElementById('score');
        const clickButton = document.getElementById('clickButton');

        clickButton.addEventListener('click', () => {
            score++;
            scoreDisplay.textContent = 'Score: ' + score;
        });
    </script>

</body>
</html>
```

### How to Use:
1. Copy the code above.
2. Paste it into a text editor and save the file with a `.html` extension (e.g., `click_game.html`).
3. Open the saved file in a web browser.
4. Click the blue button to increase your score!
